          <p>
            Timely prosthetics are especially important when even a single tooth is lost,
            as the absence of teeth leads to the shifting of adjacent units, bite
            malocclusion, overloading of chewing muscles, and gradual deformation of the
            dentition. A correctly selected orthopedic structure helps avoid these
            complications and preserves oral health for years to come.
          </p>

